body:
The following program generates an UNOPTFLAT warning which I think is incorrect. 

```systemverilog
module main (
    input logic go
);
    logic [31:0] add10_left;
    logic [31:0] add10_right;
    logic [31:0] add10_out;
    logic [31:0] add9_left;
    logic [31:0] add9_right;
    logic [31:0] add9_out;

    assign add10_out = add10_left + add10_right;
    assign add9_out = add9_left + add9_right;

    assign add10_right =
      go ? add9_out :
     ~go ? 32'd1 : 32'd0;

    assign add9_right =
      go ? 32'd1 :
     ~go ? add10_out : 32'd0;
endmodule
```

When `go = 1`, we'll have the assignments:
```
add10_right = add9_out;
add9_right = 32'd1;
```
and when `go = 0`, we'll have:
```
add10_right = 32'd1;
add9_right = add10_out;
```

Both of which don't seem to create circular logic (correct me if I'm wrong about this). 

Version: Verilator 4.200 2021-03-12 rev v4.110-43-g5022e81af (mod)

Would you be willing to try to fix Verilator yourself with assistance?
Yes, depending on the scope of the problem
